{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/information-democracy-build-trust-in-data-by-aligning-the-vision-9e311c6dfc10", "time": 1683000521.580828, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/information-democracy-build-trust-in-data-by-aligning-the-vision-9e311c6dfc10/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Information democracy, build trust in data by aligning the vision | by Wesley Nitikromo | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Information democracy, build trust in data by aligning the vision", "description": "Providing the organization with data to become data-driven sounds like a no-brainer. But when it comes to aligning the business goals to data, it gets a little more complicated. It is exactly this\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [], "all_paragraphs": ["Providing the organization with data to become data-driven sounds like a no-brainer. But when it comes to aligning the business goals to data, it gets a little more complicated. It is exactly this moment when terms like Big Data, Data Lake and Unstructured data start to show up, just as a way to express the organizations\u2019 inability to cope with the constant flow of data.", "Lots of organizations are sitting on a pile of data. Without proper semantics this data is worthless. Analyzing this data would probably require some Data Scientists to cleanse and label the data, in an effort to find some significant insights. Some organizations would even provide business users with self-service BI tools, plugging directly into the pile of data. The new ad-hoc found insights can now be \u201cproductionalized\u201d and, for example, be implemented in Machine Learning algorithms to analyze the massive pile of data and to process all the freshly generated real-time, streaming data.", "But how do we make sure these insights are aligned to the strategic goals of the organization? Should the Data Scientist elaborate on the Machine Learning model in the boardroom, or should the algorithm simply be monitored by a performance gauge in a KPI dashboard? Neither option will make sure that we always talk about the exact same metric, but how did we get to that metric? Did we really just discover something about our business by coincidence?", "Common business logic is an important starting point for analytics. Pre-defined and well-documented business metrics that make up the insights. When you have a semantic layer containing the business logic, you will be able to align the metrics to the strategic goals. This will initially help to process the data and in the long-run help to understand how to deal with the varieties of data coming in.", "The following steps provide some rough guidelines to get to this alignment:", "By following these guidelines you will start building a new single-source-of-truth. All data will now be transformed into trustworthy metrics, robust because there is a single definition that is consistent throughout the business. Acknowledging the business perspective when building these metrics, helps to validate that, insights derived from the metrics are now exactly what we\u2019re talking about. We created a basic understanding of our data.", "A single definition that is consistent throughout the business.", "When users get access to these metrics, they will immediately feel familiar. They can finally rely on the data to drive their decisions. But the best part is that from this logical business model layer, you can serve out your metrics to a broader audience as well. It enables organizations to share their view on the data.", "With this single-source-of-trustworthy-truth in place, you can start to facilitate information democracy in your organization. Providing users with self-service BI in a governed and well-designed environment will build their trust. Get to know your data from a business perspective and you can build the best information products possible. With a data warehouse now fully supporting your organization\u2019s strategic goals, you can now truly become data-driven.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "DataOps | Data Infrastructure | Experienced Business Intelligence Professional | Director of Analytics Engineering @DataBright"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F9e311c6dfc10&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Finformation-democracy-build-trust-in-data-by-aligning-the-vision-9e311c6dfc10&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Finformation-democracy-build-trust-in-data-by-aligning-the-vision-9e311c6dfc10&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/search?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Finformation-democracy-build-trust-in-data-by-aligning-the-vision-9e311c6dfc10&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Finformation-democracy-build-trust-in-data-by-aligning-the-vision-9e311